# Write commit messages in concise English.
#
# Summary (first line):
# - Keep it short (<= 50 chars), imperative mood (e.g., "Fix bug", not "Fixed bug").
# - Do not end with a period.
#
# Body (optional, after a blank line):
# - Explain the what and why, not the how.
# - Wrap at ~72 characters per line.
# - Reference issues/PRs when relevant (e.g., "Closes #123").

